<node CREATED="1527090748959" ID="ID_708132421" MODIFIED="1587247045931" TEXT="failsafe (Weakly Consistent)">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="rgb(36, 39, 41)">Typically, weak consistency means that if a collection is modified concurrently with an iteration,</font><font size="1"><br size="1" /></font><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="rgb(36, 39, 41)">the guarantees of what the iteration sees are weaker.</font><font size="1"><br size="1" /></font><font size="1" face="Arial, Helvetica Neue, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="rgb(36, 39, 41)">(The details will be specified in each conncurrent collection classes javadocs).</font>
    </p>
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
