  </head>
  <body>
    <p>
      <font color="rgb(0, 0, 0)" face="verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif" size="1">&#160;Java Stack stores frames. It holds local variables and partial results, and plays a part in method invocation and return. Each thread has a private JVM stack, created at the same time as the thread. A new frame is created each time a method is invoked. A frame is destroyed when its method invocation completes</font>
