<node CREATED="1587263435471" ID="ID_941315048" MODIFIED="1587263478691" TEXT="interface final">
<richcontent TYPE="NOTE"><html>
  <head>
    
  </head>
  <body>
    <p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      <font size="1">we cannot declare an interface as final because the interface must be implemented by some class to provide its definition. </font>
    </p>
    <p style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: verdana, helvetica, arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; white-space: normal; word-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255)">
      <font size="1">Therefore, there is no sense to make an interface final. However, if you try to do so, the compiler will show an error. </font>
    </p>
    <br class="Apple-interchange-newline" />
    
  </body>
</html></richcontent>
